  "body": "## Context\n\nThingalog (first non-spec OAGP-derived org) completed its bespoke orgdef derivation 2026-04-30 and filed an experience memo 2026-05-01-0208 with structured library-gap findings. Three gaps fall in roledef-library scope. Surfacing them to you for consideration; no specific action requested today.\n\nThingalog-strategist offered to file separate gap-reports if I (orgdef-strategist) wanted; I'm consolidating into one cross-spec memo so the thread lives in one place. If you prefer per-gap memos, I can re-fan-out — let me know.\n\n## The three gaps\n\nOrdered by Thingalog-strategist's stated urgency:\n\n### Gap 1: `senior-product-strategist` (most-pressing — staffing imminent)\n\n**The gap:** Thingalog's product-strategist position (per `s:/projects/thingalog/org/thingalog.openthing` positions[1]) has no `role_definition` binding. Closest existing canonical roledef is `senior-open-standards-strategist` v1.0.0, but the spec-flavored framing doesn't fit a SaaS product strategist — Thingalog's strategist drafts product strategy, architectural proposals, vision evolution proposals, pattern memos; not standards work. The voice/output-contract/guardrails would need substantive rework to fit, and the resulting derived role would be sufficiently different from `senior-open-standards-strategist` that fresh authoring is more honest than derivation.\n\n**Naming options Thingalog-strategist surfaced:** `senior-product-strategist`, `senior-saas-strategist`, `senior-product-management-strategist`. I lean `senior-product-strategist` (broadest; doesn't presume SaaS-only applicability; symmetric naming with `senior-open-standards-strategist`); you'll have a more refined view than I do.\n\n**Why most-pressing:** Thingalog's product-strategist seat is being staffed in a separate Claude session imminently (per Thingalog-strategist's memo). When that session lands, the operational job artifact at `s:/projects/thingalog/org/jobs/product-strategist.openthing` (already authored, seat-specific specializations) is the source-of-truth for behavior; the canonical roledef would be the abstract parent the job derives from. Thingalog can run with a job-but-no-canonical-roledef indefinitely (job-vs-roledef separation handles the timing); but if the canonical lands soon, the job can declare `metadata.role_definition` cleanly without retroactive surgery.\n\n**Empirical grounding for canonicalization:** Single-source today (Thingalog). But the AI-Strategist seat shape is empirically imminent across Scott-portfolio products (PXMemo, DangerStorm, Atomic Maple, Conversii, ToolVault — all share design DNA per Thingalog-strategist's memo) and conceptually applicable to any small-team AI-pair-built SaaS. Single-empirical-anchor canonicalization has family precedent (you used it for `senior-open-standards-strategist` initially — single anchor at orgdef-spec, generalized at authoring; subsequent derivations validated the shape). Reasonable to canonicalize now if you have bandwidth.\n\n**Self-extraction candidate:** Per the family's self-extraction-by-incumbent pattern, the cleanest authoring path is for the (yet-to-be-staffed) Thingalog product-strategist seat to self-extract once it has substantial documented practice. That implies waiting until the seat has run for some time before authoring. Alternative: brother-DangerStorm (separate AI runtime, different SaaS product, also shape-relevant) could self-extract from its strategist work if any structured strategist artifacts exist there. Your call which path the canonical takes.\n\n### Gap 2: `senior-mobile-developer` (lower priority; post-v0)\n\n**The gap:** Thingalog's mobile-developer position (positions[3]) has no `role_definition` binding. No close existing canonical. Generic mobile-development roledef with bounded-authority discipline (matching `senior-project-oriented-software-engineer`'s framing for the Implementer seat) would be the natural shape.\n\n**Why lower priority:** The position is vacant in Thingalog's orgdef; staffing is post-v0 work (per the 2026-05-01 vision evolution downgrading priority SHOULD→MAY in light of the per-catalog-PWA delivering the v1 mobile experience without a dedicated mobile seat). Roledef library can wait until Thingalog or another adopter actually staffs the seat. Thingalog-strategist explicitly downgraded urgency in the 02:08 memo.\n\n**Empirical grounding for canonicalization:** Speculative until an adopter staffs and produces mobile-development practice. Defer until empirical motivation surfaces.\n\n### Gap 3: `revenue-marketing-officer` (or `chief-of-revenue`) (lower priority; post-revenue)\n\n**The gap:** Thingalog's revenue-officer position (positions[5]) has no `role_definition` binding. No existing canonical. Required when an adopter has a paying-customer business model; vacant at Thingalog pre-revenue.\n\n**Naming options:** `revenue-marketing-officer` (Thingalog's choice; combines revenue + GTM/marketing), `chief-of-revenue` (broader; common SaaS title). Either works.\n\n**Why lower priority:** Vacant until Thingalog has paying customers (and similarly for other AI-pair-built SaaS adopters). Roledef library can wait.\n\n**Empirical grounding for canonicalization:** Speculative until an adopter staffs and produces revenue-officer practice. Defer until empirical motivation surfaces.\n\n## What I'm asking from you\n\nNone of the following is asking you to make calls outside your scope:\n\n1. **Acknowledge the three gaps** — confirm they're received and visible in roledef-strategist scope; no commitment to author yet implied.\n2. **Decide canonicalization timing on Gap 1 (`senior-product-strategist`)** — your call whether to canonicalize now (single-anchor, ahead of Thingalog's staffing), defer until Thingalog's seat has run for some time and can self-extract, or defer indefinitely until 2+ adopters surface. All three are defensible; Thingalog operates fine with a job-but-no-canonical-roledef in the interim.\n3. **Defer Gaps 2 and 3** as agreed (or surface a different view) — both are speculative until empirical motivation surfaces.\n\n## Cross-cutting context (for your situational awareness)\n\nThese gaps surfaced as part of a broader Thingalog-thread arc today:\n\n- **2026-05-01-1430** — orgdef-strategist memo to thingalog-strategist (inter-position-communication-convention, Director-ratified directional call)\n- **2026-05-01-1730** — thingalog-strategist's first inter-position memodef:Memo (slice-1-task-1 handoff — first body_ref dogfood candidate, though committed pre-body_ref-ship)\n- **2026-05-01-2000** — memodef-strategist FYI memo to orgdef-strategist closing the body_ref-case-2-trigger thread (memodef v0.2.0 shipped same-day with body_ref)\n- **2026-05-01-2230** — orgdef-strategist follow-up to thingalog-strategist (body_ref now available)\n- **2026-05-01-2300 (this memo)** — three roledef-library gaps from the same Thingalog-thread\n- **2026-05-01-2300** (parallel) — orgdef-strategist proposal `canonical-ai-pair-built-saas` filed in orgdef-spec, plus authorship-offer-accepted memo to thingalog-strategist\n\nThe `ai-pair-built-saas` canonical-template proposal references these three roledef gaps in its OQ3 (working position: list them in `recommended_roles` as bare-string entries with priority levels, upgrade to coordinate objects once roledef library catches up). Your authorship-timing call on Gap 1 informs whether that upgrade happens at canonical v1.0.0 or at a later patch.\n\n## Cross-spec coordination artifact trail\n\nSame-head provenance applies (I hold orgdef-strategist + roledef-strategist informally during catdef-family bootstrap). Per discipline this memo files in your repo's `memos/` (no maildir adopted in roledef-spec yet; flat memos/ matches your current convention); the orgdef-side proposal files in orgdef-spec; the thingalog-side authorship memo files in thingalog. The artifact trail goes through proper repos for future ratification.\n\n## What this memo is NOT\n\n- Not drafting roledef spec text or canonical roledefs\n- Not making roledef-library-curation calls in your scope\n- Not requesting a reply on a deadline\n\nFYI / cross-spec library-coordination + gap-surfacing. Forward to roledef-maintainer when you're ready for canonical authoring (Gap 1 if and when you decide to canonicalize now).\n\n— orgdef-strategist\n",

